      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 14
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is an exceptional FD3S RX-7, showcasing the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW rotary powerplant, featuring the complex sequential twin-turbocharger setup with seamless transition and robust boost pressure. The chassis dynamics are preserved via the factory-spec double-wishbone aluminum suspension and a perfectly balanced 50/50 weight distribution. Mechanically, the vehicle has undergone a comprehensive refresh of the critical vacuum line assembly and the apex seals show exceptional compression numbers across all faces. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a Torsen limited-slip differential. The exterior retains its factory-applied finish with no signs of oxidation or clear coat failure, while the interior plastics and upholstery remain free of the typical UV degradation. This is a collector-grade example for the discerning rotary purist.",
